snippet: Alexander Dale Oen of Norway, the reigning world champion in the 100-meter breaststroke, died of cardiac arrest while in Flagstaff, Ariz., training with the Norwegian national team. He was 26.
abstract: Norwegian swimmer Alexander Dale Oen, 26-year-old reigning world champion in the 100-meter breaststroke, dies of cardiac arrest while training in Flagstaff, Ariz, for the 2012 Olympics.
lead_paragraph: Alexander Dale Oen of Norway, the reigning world champion in the 100-meter breaststroke, died of cardiac arrest while in Flagstaff, Ariz., training with the Norwegian national team. He was 26.

headline.seo: Norwegian Swimmer Alexander Dale Oen Dies at 26
headline.main: Champion Swimmer Found Dead in Arizona
